entry.summary: Today I am writing about Population though my last two post were also about population .But, today in this post i will analyse the data and make some visuals using the data and find some answers. In this blog i am going to use dataset from the UN databank (Link:http://data.un.org/

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h6 id="Today-I-am-writing-about-Population-though-my-last-two-post-were-also-about-population-.But,-today-in-this-post-i-will-analyse-the-data--and-make-some-visuals-using-the-data-and-find-some-answers.-In-this-blog-i-am-going-to-use-dataset-from-the-UN-databank-(Link:http://data.un.org/).-This-dataset-is-about-the-world-population-from-1950-to-2015.It-has-the-population-data-of-all-the-Continents,Country.I-am-using-python-to-read-this-dataset-and-have-a-look-in-the-CSV-file.I-am-using-Numpy--for-analysis-or-for-arithematic-and-Matplotlib-for-visualization-of-data-and-Jupyter-Notebook-as-my-Python-workspace.I-am-using-only-the-contents-of--6-Contients(#Note:exclude-Antractica-there-is-no-permanent-settlement)-and-population-of-world-for-analysis-and-following-are-the-code-i-wrote-for-it.">Today I am writing about Population though my last two post were also about population .But, today in this post i will analyse the data  and make some visuals using the data and find some answers. In this blog i am going to use dataset from the UN databank (Link:<a href="http://data.un.org/">http://data.un.org/</a>). This dataset is about the world population from 1950 to 2015.It has the population data of all the Continents,Country.I am using python to read this dataset and have a look in the CSV file.I am using Numpy  for analysis or for arithematic and Matplotlib for visualization of data and Jupyter Notebook as my Python workspace.I am using only the contents of  6 Contients(#Note:exclude Antractica there is no permanent settlement) and population of world for analysis and following are the code i wrote for it.<a class="anchor-link" href="#Today-I-am-writing-about-Population-though-my-last-two-post-were-also-about-population-.But,-today-in-this-post-i-will-analyse-the-data--and-make-some-visuals-using-the-data-and-find-some-answers.-In-this-blog-i-am-going-to-use-dataset-from-the-UN-databank-(Link:http://data.un.org/).-This-dataset-is-about-the-world-population-from-1950-to-2015.It-has-the-population-data-of-all-the-Continents,Country.I-am-using-python-to-read-this-dataset-and-have-a-look-in-the-CSV-file.I-am-using-Numpy--for-analysis-or-for-arithematic-and-Matplotlib-for-visualization-of-data-and-Jupyter-Notebook-as-my-Python-workspace.I-am-using-only-the-contents-of--6-Contients(#Note:exclude-Antractica-there-is-no-permanent-settlement)-and-population-of-world-for-analysis-and-following-are-the-code-i-wrote-for-it.">¶</a></h6>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [7]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">#Importing required python packages NUMPY and MATPLOTLIB</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">numpy</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">np</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>

<span class="c1">#using python to load the csv file</span>
<span class="n">f</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"population data.csv"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"r"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">rows</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'</span><span class="se">\n</span><span class="s1">'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">final_data</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[]</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h6 id='In-following-code-i-used-function-"region"-to-get-the-data-of-continent-according-to-their-name-by-searching-in-the-list-called-"rows"--and-another-function-"Interize"-to-convert-the-string-value-in-list-to-Integer.'>In following code i used function "region" to get the data of continent according to their name by searching in the list called "rows"  and another function "Interize" to convert the string value in list to Integer.<a class="anchor-link" href='#In-following-code-i-used-function-"region"-to-get-the-data-of-continent-according-to-their-name-by-searching-in-the-list-called-"rows"--and-another-function-"Interize"-to-convert-the-string-value-in-list-to-Integer.'>¶</a></h6>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [8]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">#Function to get the data from CSV file using the parameter name to search data using loop in given list of data</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">region</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">R_name</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">final_data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span> <span class="c1"># a list which will hold the data taken from rows list for some time</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">pop_data</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">rows</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="c1"># loop to search the row in list rows, we split the data after ","  and append in final_data</span>
        <span class="n">pop</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pop_data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">','</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">final_data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pop</span><span class="p">)</span>   
    <span class="n">Region_data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span> <span class="c1"># Declaring new list which will </span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">datum</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">final_data</span><span class="p">:</span>
         <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">R_name</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">datum</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">Region_data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">datum</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">Region_data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Region_data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:]</span> <span class="c1"># Region_data has list in list so to have only one list data</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">Region_data</span>
<span class="n">World</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">region</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">R_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"WORLD"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Africa</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">region</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">R_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"AFRICA"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Asia</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">region</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">R_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"ASIA"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Europe</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">region</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">R_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"EUROPE"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Latinamerica</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">region</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">R_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"LATIN AMERICA AND THE CARIBBEAN"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">NorthAmerica</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">region</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">R_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"NORTHERN AMERICA"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Oceania</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">region</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">R_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"OCEANIA"</span><span class="p">)</span>


<span class="c1">#function to make the string data in list to Integer</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">Interize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">List</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">lone_list</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">data</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">List</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">lone_list</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">))</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">lone_list</span>
<span class="n">Africa</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Interize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Africa</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Asia</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Interize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Asia</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Europe</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">Interize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Europe</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Latinamerica</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">Interize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Latinamerica</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">NorthAmerica</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">Interize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">NorthAmerica</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Oceania</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">Interize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Oceania</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">World</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Interize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">World</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"----World-----"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">World</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"-----AFRICA------"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Africa</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"----ASIA-----"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Asia</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"----Europe----"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Europe</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"----Latin America-----"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Latinamerica</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"----North America-----"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">NorthAmerica</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"-----Oceania------"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Oceania</span><span class="p">)</span>
       
</pre></div>

<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [9]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">#making a Year list which will be used to visualize in graphs  </span>
<span class="n">year</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1950</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">2020</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"year"</span><span class="p">),</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="p">)</span>

[1950 1955 1960 1965 1970 1975 1980 1985 1990 1995 2000 2005 2010 2015]

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [10]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">#using .plot to plot a graph using the population value and year value</span>
<span class="c1">#</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">figure</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">8.5</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="c1">#a function to plot the graph which has two argument time_line as x and region as y </span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">ploting</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">time_line</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Region_name</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">mark</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">time_line</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Region_name</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">marker</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">mark</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
<span class="n">ploting</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Asia</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"*"</span><span class="p">)</span>    
<span class="n">ploting</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Africa</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"o"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<h6 id="In-above-plot-we-can-see-the-size-of-population-of--continents-from-1950-to-2015-using-the-legend-and-graphs-plot.This-plot-is-using-Year-as-X-axis-and-Population-in-Thousand-as-Y-axis.-We-can-see-the-all-continent's-population-is-increasing--but-the-Europe's-is-starting-to-decrease-from-year-1995.It-may-seems-population-of-Oceania-reagion-is-Zero-but-not-as-the-population-of-australia-is-very-small-and-this-graph-is-using-population-in-thousand-basis-so-it-seems-Oceania-is-zero.">In above plot we can see the size of population of  continents from 1950 to 2015 using the legend and graphs plot.This plot is using Year as X-axis and Population in Thousand as Y-axis. We can see the all continent's population is increasing  but the Europe's is starting to decrease from year 1995.It may seems population of Oceania reagion is Zero but not as the population of australia is very small and this graph is using population in thousand basis so it seems Oceania is zero.<a class="anchor-link" href="#In-above-plot-we-can-see-the-size-of-population-of--continents-from-1950-to-2015-using-the-legend-and-graphs-plot.This-plot-is-using-Year-as-X-axis-and-Population-in-Thousand-as-Y-axis.-We-can-see-the-all-continent's-population-is-increasing--but-the-Europe's-is-starting-to-decrease-from-year-1995.It-may-seems-population-of-Oceania-reagion-is-Zero-but-not-as-the-population-of-australia-is-very-small-and-this-graph-is-using-population-in-thousand-basis-so-it-seems-Oceania-is-zero.">¶</a></h6>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">#Making pizza chart or pac_man chart</span>

<span class="n">pop_sizes_2015</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">4384844</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1166239</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">743123</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">630089</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">361128</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">39359</span> <span class="p">]</span>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h6 id='This-Pie-Chart-shows-us-the-population-size-of-every-continents-in-year-2015.It-shows-us-the-population-of-"Asia"-is-more-than-double-combining-all-the-remaining-continents.This-graph-look-like-a-pizza-where-Asia-has-biggest-share-of-pizza."Oceania"-has-only-0.5%-of-whole-world-population.'>This Pie-Chart shows us the population size of every continents in year 2015.It shows us the population of "Asia" is more than double combining all the remaining continents.This graph look like a pizza where Asia has biggest share of pizza."Oceania" has only 0.5% of whole world population.<a class="anchor-link" href='#This-Pie-Chart-shows-us-the-population-size-of-every-continents-in-year-2015.It-shows-us-the-population-of-"Asia"-is-more-than-double-combining-all-the-remaining-continents.This-graph-look-like-a-pizza-where-Asia-has-biggest-share-of-pizza."Oceania"-has-only-0.5%-of-whole-world-population.'>¶</a></h6>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [22]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># rate of increase in population in 5 yrs</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">inc_pop_rate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">a</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">b</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">rate</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">((</span><span class="n">a</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">b</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">a</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="mi">100</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">rate</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">rate_find</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Conti</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">lists</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">):</span>
        <span class="n">lists</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">inc_pop_rate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Conti</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">Conti</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">]))</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">lists</span> 
<span class="n">Africa_list</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">rate_find</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Africa</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Asia_list</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">rate_find</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Asia</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Europe_list</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">rate_find</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Europe</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Latinamerica_list</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">rate_find</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Latinamerica</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">NorthAmerica_list</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">rate_find</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">NorthAmerica</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">Oceania_list</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">rate_find</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Oceania</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">World_list</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">rate_find</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">World</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">year_new</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">year</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">14</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"year 1955-2015"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year_new</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

[1955 1960 1965 1970 1975 1980 1985 1990 1995 2000 2005 2010 2015]

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [13]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">figure</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">16</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">8</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">labels</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'Asia'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'Africa'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'Europe'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'Latinamerica'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'NorthAmerica'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'Oceania'</span>
<span class="n">ploting</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year_new</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Asia_list</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"o"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ploting</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year_new</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Africa_list</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"*"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ploting</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year_new</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Europe_list</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"o"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ploting</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year_new</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Latinamerica_list</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"*"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ploting</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year_new</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">NorthAmerica_list</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"o"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ploting</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">year_new</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Oceania_list</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"*"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">labels</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loc</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"best"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Population increasing rate per five year from 1955 to 2015"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"red"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>This graph plot is about the population growth rate per five years of continents.Thepopulation growth rate  of Europe is decreasing over the year slowly. The population increase rate is high for Africa and it will increase Africa's  population.Though Oceania has Smallest population but it has second highest increasing rate.The high population increase rate of Asia is slowing down its seems the effect of economic boobs in some Asia country.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [14]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="sd">"""for density of population in continents we are taking the area in km.Sq </span>
<span class="sd">in list according to the population increasing order"""</span>

<span class="n">Area_km</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="p">{</span><span class="s2">"Asia"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">43820000</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"Africa"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">30370000</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"Europe"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">10180000</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"Latinamerica"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">17840000</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"Northamerica"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">24490000</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"Oceania"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">9008500</span><span class="p">}</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">density</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pop</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">area</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">dense</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">pops</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">pop</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">dense</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pops</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">area</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">dense</span>
<span class="n">Asia_den</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">density</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Asia</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Area_km</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Asia"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">Africa_den</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">density</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Africa</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Area_km</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Africa"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">Europe_den</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">density</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Europe</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Area_km</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Europe"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">LatinAmerica_den</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">density</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Latinamerica</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Area_km</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Latinamerica"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">NorthAmerica_den</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">density</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">NorthAmerica</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Area_km</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Northamerica"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">Oceania_den</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">density</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">Oceania</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">Area_km</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Oceania"</span><span class="p">])</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h6 id="In-following-code-we-are-plotting-a-bar-diagram-with-6-multiple-datas.In-the-plt.bar()--i-used-year-as-X-axis-and-to-print-Six-data-in-that-one-x-axis-point-it-is-needed-to-move-the-bar-so-all-6-bar-can-be-shown.To-show-all-bar-i-added-0.6-to-every-bar-to-print-the-bar-in-new-poition-so-it-will-disturb-other-bars.">In following code we are plotting a bar diagram with 6 multiple datas.In the plt.bar()  i used year as X-axis and to print Six data in that one x-axis point it is needed to move the bar so all 6 bar can be shown.To show all bar i added 0.6 to every bar to print the bar in new poition so it will disturb other bars.<a class="anchor-link" href="#In-following-code-we-are-plotting-a-bar-diagram-with-6-multiple-datas.In-the-plt.bar()--i-used-year-as-X-axis-and-to-print-Six-data-in-that-one-x-axis-point-it-is-needed-to-move-the-bar-so-all-6-bar-can-be-shown.To-show-all-bar-i-added-0.6-to-every-bar-to-print-the-bar-in-new-poition-so-it-will-disturb-other-bars.">¶</a></h6>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [15]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">figure</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">18</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">))</span><span class="c1"># size of plotting field</span>
<span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1950</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">2020</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">bar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Asia_den</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'blue'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">width</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.6</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">bar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mf">0.6</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Africa_den</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'brown'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">width</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.6</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">bar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mf">1.2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Europe_den</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'orange'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">width</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.6</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">bar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mf">1.8</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">LatinAmerica_den</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'green'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">width</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.6</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">bar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mf">2.4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">NorthAmerica_den</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'gold'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">width</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.6</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">bar</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">Oceania_den</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'red'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">width</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.6</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">labels</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'Asia'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'Africa'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'Europe'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'LatinAmerica'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'NorthAmerica'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s1">'Oceania'</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Population Density in Continents"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"red"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Years"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">12</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"green"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Thousand/KM.Sq"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">12</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"blue"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">labels</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">loc</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"best"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">show</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>

<h6 id="In-above-plot-we-can-see-the-density-of-population-over-period-of-time-in-Continents.In-todays-time-dense-continent-is-Asia-it-left-europe-behind-in-1990-and-Europe-is-2nd-dense-continent.Oceania-is-least-dense-country-as-its-land-area-is-big-comparable-to-Europe-but-population-is-very-small.">In above plot we can see the density of population over period of time in Continents.In todays time dense continent is Asia it left europe behind in 1990 and Europe is 2nd dense continent.Oceania is least dense country as its land area is big comparable to Europe but population is very small.<a class="anchor-link" href="#In-above-plot-we-can-see-the-density-of-population-over-period-of-time-in-Continents.In-todays-time-dense-continent-is-Asia-it-left-europe-behind-in-1990-and-Europe-is-2nd-dense-continent.Oceania-is-least-dense-country-as-its-land-area-is-big-comparable-to-Europe-but-population-is-very-small.">¶</a></h6>

<h6 id="The-above-plot-is-about-the-population-of-whole-world.The-graph-shows-that-the-population-of-world-increased-in-very-high-rate-over-last-50-years.The-population-of-world-was-2525779-thousand-in-1950-and-it-became-more-than-double-i.e-7324782-thousand-over-period-of-65-years-in-2015.">The above plot is about the population of whole world.The graph shows that the population of world increased in very high rate over last 50 years.The population of world was 2525779 thousand in 1950 and it became more than double i.e 7324782 thousand over period of 65 years in 2015.<a class="anchor-link" href="#The-above-plot-is-about-the-population-of-whole-world.The-graph-shows-that-the-population-of-world-increased-in-very-high-rate-over-last-50-years.The-population-of-world-was-2525779-thousand-in-1950-and-it-became-more-than-double-i.e-7324782-thousand-over-period-of-65-years-in-2015.">¶</a></h6>

entry.title: US Immigration
entry.summary:
US Imigration analysis 1980-2013(SAARC)¶

In this program i am going to read data about the no of migrants in US from all around the globe from 1980 to 2013 taken from https://esa.un.org/unpd/wpp/Download/Standard/Migration/ and loaded in python. I am filtering data from given data and only using data of SAARC countries(Afganistan,Bangladesh,Bhutan,India,Maldives,Nepal,Pakistan,Srilanka).In this program i am using matplotlib python package to visualize the given data.The data i will use is No of people moved to US in given Years from their homeland.

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h1 id="US-Imigration-analysis-1980-2013(SAARC)">US Imigration analysis 1980-2013(SAARC)<a class="anchor-link" href="#US-Imigration-analysis-1980-2013(SAARC)">¶</a></h1><p>In this program i am going to read data about the no of migrants in  US from all around the globe from 1980 to 2013 taken from  <a href="https://esa.un.org/unpd/wpp/Download/Standard/Migration/">https://esa.un.org/unpd/wpp/Download/Standard/Migration/</a> and loaded in python. I am filtering data from given data and only using data of SAARC countries(Afganistan,Bangladesh,Bhutan,India,Maldives,Nepal,Pakistan,Srilanka).In this program i am using matplotlib python package to visualize the given data.The data i will use is No of people moved to US in given Years from their homeland.</p>
<p>I have used python to read data and took the data of only 8 saarc country using function "country(C_name)".I used matplotlib python package to visualize the extracted data to find out how was the no of migrants to US from these * nations from 1980 to 2013.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [3]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">#Importing packages</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>

<span class="c1">#using python to load the csv file</span>
<span class="n">f</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"C:/Users/Diwash/Desktop/United States of Americ.csv"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s2">"r"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">f</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">rows</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'</span><span class="se">\n</span><span class="s1">'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">final_data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">imi_data</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">rows</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">imig</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">imi_data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">','</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">final_data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">imig</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
<span class="c1">#function to find the data for required country from the file.using this functionwe will get no. of  </span>
<span class="c1">#immigrants from 1980 to 2013 from that country and will be saved as full_data and return to function caller</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">country</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">C_name</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="n">final_data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">imi_data</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">rows</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">imig</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">imi_data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">','</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="n">final_data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">imig</span><span class="p">)</span>    
    <span class="n">Country_data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">datum</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">final_data</span><span class="p">:</span>
         <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">C_name</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">datum</span><span class="p">:</span>
             <span class="n">Country_data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">datum</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">Country_data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Country_data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">:]</span>
    <span class="n">full_data</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">ndatas</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">Country_data</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">full_data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ndatas</span><span class="p">))</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">full_data</span><span class="p">)</span>    


<span class="c1"># we are getting the years 1980 to 2013 and appending in variable which is list</span>
<span class="n">years_data</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="n">final_data</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">:]</span>
<span class="n">year</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">years</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">years_data</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="n">year</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">years</span><span class="p">))</span>
       
<span class="c1">#calling the function for country data and saving in their respective name</span>
<span class="n">nepal</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">country</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">C_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"Nepal"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">india</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">country</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">C_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"India"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">afgan</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">country</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">C_name</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"Afghanistan"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1">#importing the package </span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>

<span class="c1">#import population and the years </span>
<span class="n">population</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mf">5.85</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">6.60</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">7.10</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">7.91</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">9.78</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">12.62</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">16.50</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">25.21</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">60.08</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">67.07</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">68.96</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">70.52</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">97.25</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mf">97.46</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">years</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1500</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1600</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1700</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1750</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1800</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1850</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1900</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1950</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1999</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">2008</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">2010</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">2012</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">2050</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">2150</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">n_population</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">population</span> 
<span class="c1">#fill the grap with color for better  visualization</span>



<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">show</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Years in AD'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Population in terms of Ten Million'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'World Population Projections'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">years</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">population</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'green'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">scatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">years</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">population</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">edgecolors</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'black'</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">s</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">population</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">c</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'red'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">savefig</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'plot.png'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">show</span><span class="p">()</span>
</pre></div>
